Sugarcane Millet Kheer

Method: Soak 90-100 grams of barnyard millet (Isha Life) @isha.life.india for 8 hours. Soaking is essential as it aids digestion due to the high fibre content.

Start cooking by boiling 1 litre of fresh sugarcane juice. Remove the scum after the first boil. Drain the soaked millets and add them to the boiling juice along with 1.5 teaspoons of fennel seeds (you can use the drained soaking water to make any vegetable dish, dal, or chapati dough).

This cooking process will take 25-30 minutes. Once the grains are soft after 25 minutes, add 500 ml of coconut milk and simmer for another 10 minutes.

Finish with coconut flakes and fried cashews. Enjoy it straight from the pan!
